<worksheet label="ws-act-5-5-1">
  <activity xml:id="act-5-5-1">
    <introduction>
      <p>
      For each of the following problems,
      evaluate the integral by using the partial fraction decomposition provided.

      </p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="act-5-5-1-task-0">
      <statement>
        <p><m>\int \frac{1}{x^2 - 2x - 3} \, dx</m>,
            given that <m>\frac{1}{x^2 - 2x - 3} = \frac{1/4}{x-3} - \frac{1/4}{x+1}</m></p>
      </statement>
      <hint>
        <p><m>\int \frac{1}{u} \, du = \ln|u| + C</m>.
          </p>
      </hint>
      <answer>
        <p><m>\int \frac{1}{x^2 - 2x - 3} \, dx = \frac{1}{4}\ln|x-3| - \frac{1}{4}\ln|x+1| + C</m>.
          </p>
      </answer>
      <solution>
        <p><m>\int \frac{1}{x^2 - 2x - 3} \, dx = \int \frac{1/4}{x-3} - \frac{1/4}{x+1} \, dx = \frac{1}{4}\ln|x-3| - \frac{1}{4}\ln|x+1| + C</m>.
          </p>
      </solution>
    </task>
    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="act-5-5-1-task-1">
      <statement>
        <p><m>\int \frac{x^2+1}{x^3 - x^2} \, dx</m>,
            given that <m>\frac{x^2+1}{x^3 - x^2} = -\frac{1}{x} - \frac{1}{x^2} + \frac{2}{x-1}</m></p>
      </statement>
      <hint>
        <p><m>\frac{1}{x^2} = x^{-2}</m>.
          </p>
      </hint>
      <answer>
        <p><m>\int \frac{x^2+1}{x^3 - x^2} \, dx = -\ln|x| + x^{-1} + 2\ln|x-1| + C</m>.
          </p>
      </answer>
      <solution>
        <p><m>\int \frac{x^2+1}{x^3 - x^2} \, dx = \int\left(-\frac{1}{x} - \frac{1}{x^2} + \frac{2}{x-1} \right) \, dx = -ln|x| + x^{-1} + 2\ln|x-1| + C</m>.
          </p>
      </solution>
    </task>
    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="act-5-5-1-task-2">
      <statement>
        <p><m>\int \frac{x-2}{x^4 + x^2}\, dx</m>,
            given that <m>\frac{x-2}{x^4 + x^2} = \frac{1}{x} - \frac{2}{x^2} + \frac{-x+2}{1+x^2}</m></p>
      </statement>
      <hint>
        <p><m>\frac{-x+2}{1+x^2} = \frac{-x}{1+x^2}+\frac{2}{1+x^2}</m>,
          </p>
      </hint>
      <answer>
        <p><m>\int \frac{x-2}{x^4 + x^2}\, dx = \ln|x| + 2x^{-1} - \frac{1}{2} \ln|1+x^2| + 2\arctan(x) + C</m>.
          </p>
      </answer>
      <solution>
        <p>
            By the partial fractions decomposition,
            <m>\int \frac{x-2}{x^4 + x^2}\, dx = \int \frac{1}{x} - \frac{2}{x^2} + \frac{-x+2}{1+x^2} \, dx </m>.
            Observing that <m>\frac{-x+2}{1+x^2} = \frac{-x}{1+x^2}+\frac{2}{1+x^2}</m>,
            it now follows that
            <me>
              \int \frac{x-2}{x^4 + x^2}\, dx = \int \frac{1}{x} - \frac{2}{x^2} - \frac{x}{1+x^2} + \frac{2}{1+x^2} \, dx
            </me>.
            Noting that <m>\int \frac{x}{1+x^2} \, dx</m> can be evaluated by the <m>u</m>-substitution <m>u=1+x^2</m>,
            we see that <m>\int \frac{x}{1+x^2} \, dx = \frac{1}{2} \ln|1+x^2| + C</m>.
            Thus
            <me>
              \int \frac{x-2}{x^4 + x^2}\, dx = \int \frac{1}{x} - \frac{2}{x^2} - \frac{x}{1+x^2} + \frac{2}{1+x^2} \, dx = \ln|x| + 2x^{-1} - \frac{1}{2} \ln|1+x^2| + 2\arctan(x) + C
            </me>.
          </p>
      </solution>
    </task>
  </activity>
</worksheet>
